h4301.definition: or מַטְמֹן; or מַטְמֻן; from {{h2934}}; a secret storehouse; hence, a secreted valuable (buried); generally money; hidden riches, (hid) treasure(-s).

h4302.definition: from {{h5193}}; something planted, i.e. the place (a garden or vineyard), or the thing (a plant, figuratively or men); by implication, the act, planting; plant(-ation, -ing).

h4303.definition: or (feminine) מַטְעַמָּה; from {{h2938}}; a delicacy; dainty (meat), savoury meat.

h4304.definition: from {{h2946}}; a wide cloak (for a woman); vail, wimple.

h4305.definition: a primitive root; to rain; (cause to) rain (upon).

h4307.definition: or מַטָּרָה; from {{h5201}}; a jail (as a guard-house); also an aim (as being closely watched); mark, prison.

h4308.definition: from {{h2956}}; propulsive; Matred, an Edomitess; Matred.

h4309.definition: from {{h4305}}; rainy; Matri, an Israelite; Matri.

h4310.definition: an interrogative pronoun of persons, as {{h4100}} is of things,; who? (occasionally, by a peculiar idiom, of things); also (indefinitely) whoever; often used in oblique construction with prefix or suffix; any (man), × he, × him,   O that! what, which, who(-m, -se, -soever),   would to God.

h4311.definition: from {{h4325}} and {{h1679}}; water of quiet; Medeba, a place in Palestine; Medeba.

h4312.definition: from {{h3032}} in the sense of loving; affectionate; Medad, an Israelite; Medad.

h4313.definition: from {{h4325}} and {{h3420}} with the art. interposed; water of the yellowness; Me-haj-Jarkon, a place in Palestine; Me-jarkon.

h4314.definition: from {{h4325}} and {{h2091}}, water of gold; Me-Zahab, an Edomite; Mezahab.

h4316.definition: a variation for {{h4318}}; Mica, the name of two Israelites; Micha.

h4317.definition: from {{h4310}} and (the prefix derivative from) {{h3588}} and {{h410}}; who (is) like God?; Mikael, the name of an archangel and of nine Israelites; Michael.

h4318.definition: an abbreviated form of {{h4320}}; Micah, the name of seven Israelites; Micah, Micaiah, Michah.

h4319.definition: a contr. for {{h4321}}; Mikehu, an Israelite prophet; Micaiah (2 Chronicles 18:8).

h4320.definition: from {{h4310}} and (the prefix derivative from) {{h3588}} and {{h3050}}; who (is) like Jah?; Micajah, the name of two Israelites; Micah, Michaiah. Compare {{h4318}}.

h4321.definition: or מִכָיְהוּ; (Jeremiah 36:11), abbreviated form for {{h4322}}; Mikajah, the name of three Israelites; Micah, Micaiah, Michaiah.

h4322.definition: for {{h4320}}; Mikajah, the name of an Israelite and an Israelitess; Michaiah.

h4323.definition: from {{h3201}}; properly, a container, i.e. a streamlet; brook.

h4324.definition: apparently the same as {{h4323}}; revulet; Mikal, Saul's daughter; Michal.

h4325.definition: dual of a primitive noun (but used in a singular sense); water; figuratively, juice; by euphemism, urine, semen; piss, wasting, water(-ing, (-course, -flood, -spring)).

h4326.definition: a form for {{h4509}}; Mijamin, the name of three Israelites; Miamin, Mijamin.

h4327.definition: from an unused root meaning to portion out; a sort, i.e. species; kind. Compare {{h4480}}.

h4328.definition: properly, feminine passive participle of {{h3245}}; something founded, i.e. a foundation; foundation.

h4331.definition: from {{h4185}}; departure; Mesha, a place in Arabia; also an Israelite; Mesha.

h4332.definition: from {{h4310}} and {{h410}} with the abbreviated form insep. relatively (see {{h834}}) interposed; who (is) what God (is) ?; Mishael, the name of three Israelites; Mishael.

h4333.definition: (Aramaic) corresponding to {{h4332}}; Mishael, an Israelite; Mishael.

h4334.definition: or מִישֹׁר; from {{h3474}}; a level, i.e. a plain (often used (with the article prefix) as a proper name of certain districts); figuratively, concord; also straightness, i.e. (figuratively) justice (sometimes adverbially, justly); equity, even place, plain, right(-eously), (made) straight, uprightness.

h4335.definition: borrowed from {{h4336}}; Meshak, an Israelite; Meshak.

h4336.definition: (Aramaic) of foreign origin and doubtful significance; name of {{h4333}}; Meshak, the Babylonian; Meshak.

h4337.definition: from {{h3467}}; safety; Mesha, an Israelite; Mesha.

h4338.definition: a variation for {{h4337}}; safety; Mesha, a Moabite; Mesha.

h4339.definition: from {{h3474}}; evenness, i.e. (figuratively) prosperity or concord; also straightness, i.e. (figuratively) rectitude (only in plural with singular sense; often adverbially); agreement, aright, that are equal, equity, (things that are) right(-eously, things), sweetly, upright(-ly, -ness).

h4340.definition: from {{h3498}}; (compare {{h3499}}); a cord (of a tent); or the string (of a bow); cord, string.

h4341.definition: sometimes מַכְאוֹב; also (feminine Isaiah 53:3) מַכְאֹבָה; from {{h3510}}; anguish or (figuratively) affliction; grief, pain, sorrow.

h4343.definition: from the same as {{h3522}}; knoll; Macbena, a place in Palestine settled by him; Machbenah.

h4344.definition: patrial from {{h4343}}; a Macbannite or native of Macbena; Machbanai.

h4345.definition: from {{h3527}} in the sense of covering (compare {{h3531}}); a grate; grate.

h4346.definition: from {{h3527}} in the sense of covering; (compare {{h4345}}); a cloth (as netted); thick cloth.

h4347.definition: or (masculine) מַכֶּה; (plural only) from {{h5221}}; a blow (in 2 Chronicles 2:10, of the flail); by implication, a wound; figuratively, carnage, also pestilence; beaten, blow, plague, slaughter, smote, × sore, stripe, stroke, wound(-ed).

h4348.definition: from {{h3554}}; a burn; that burneth, burning.

h4349.definition: from {{h3559}}; properly, a fixture, i.e. a basis; generally a place, especially as an abode; foundation, habitation, (dwelling-, settled) place.

h4350.definition: or מְכֹנָה; feminine of {{h4349}}; a pedestal, also a spot; base.

h4351.definition: or מְכֹרָה; from the same as {{h3564}} in the sense of dipping; origin (as if a mine); birth, habitation, nativity.

h4352.definition: probably from {{h4134}}; pining; Maki, an Israelite; Machi.

h4353.definition: from {{h4376}}; salesman; Makir, an Israelite; Machir.

h4354.definition: patronymical from {{h4353}}; a Makirite or descendant of Makir; of Machir.

h4355.definition: a primitive root; to tumble (in ruins); figuratively, to perish; be brought low, decay.

h4356.definition: or מִכְלָה; from {{h3607}}; a pen (for flocks); (sheep-)fold. Compare {{h4357}}.

h4357.definition: from {{h3615}}; completion (in plural concrete adverbial, wholly); perfect. Compare {{h4356}}.

h4358.definition: from {{h3634}}; perfection (i.e. concrete adverbial, splendidly); most gorgeously, all sorts.

h4360.definition: from {{h3634}}; something perfect, i.e. a splendid garment; all sorts.

h4362.definition: from the same as {{h3646}} in the sense of hiding; treasure (as hidden); treasure.

h4363.definition: (Ezra 2:2 or מִכְמָשׁ; or מִכְמַשׁ; (Nehemiah 11:31), from {{h3647}}; hidden; Mikmas or Mikmash, a place in Palestine; Mikmas, Mikmash.

h4364.definition: or מִכְמֹר; from {{h3648}} in the sense of blackening by heat; a (hunter's) net (as dark from concealment); net.

h4365.definition: or מִכְמֹרֶת; feminine of {{h4364}}; a (fisher's) net; drag, net.

h4366.definition: apparently from an unused root meaning to hide; concealment; Mikmethath, a place in Palestine; Michmethath.

h4367.definition: from {{h4100}} and {{h5068}} with a particle interposed; what (is) like (a) liberal (man) ?; Maknadbai, an Israelite; Machnadebai.

h4368.definition: the same as {{h4350}}; a base; Mekonah, a place in Palestine; Mekonah.

h4369.definition: the same as {{h4350}}; a spot; base.

h4370.definition: from {{h3647}} in the sense of hiding; (only in dual) drawers (from concealing the private parts); breeches.

h4371.definition: probably from an unused root meaning to enumerate; an assessment (as based upon a census); tribute.

h4372.definition: from {{h3680}}; a covering, i.e. weatherboarding; covering.

h4373.definition: feminine of {{h4371}}; an enumeration; by implication, a valuation; number, worth.

h4374.definition: from {{h3680}}; a covering, i.e. garment; specifically, a coverlet (for a bed), an awning (from the sun); also the omentum (as covering the intestines); clothing, to cover, that which covereth.

h4375.definition: from {{h3717}}; a fold; Makpelah, a place in Palestine; Machpelah.

h4376.definition: a primitive root; to sell, literally (as merchandise, a daughter in marriage, into slavery), or figuratively (to surrender); × at all, sell (away, -er, self).

h4377.definition: from {{h4376}}; merchandise; also value; pay, price, ware.

h4380.definition: probably from the same as {{h3564}} in the sense of stabbing; a sword; habitation.

h4381.definition: from {{h4376}}; salesman; Mikri, an Israelite; Michri.

h4382.definition: patrial from an unused name (the same as {{h4380}}) of a place in Palestine; a Mekerathite, or inhabitant of Mekerah; Mecherathite.

h4383.definition: or מִכְשֹׁל; masculine from {{h3782}}; a stumbling-block, literally or figuratively (obstacle, enticement (specifically an idol), scruple); caused to fall, offence, × (no-) thing offered, ruin, stumbling-block.

h4384.definition: feminine from {{h3782}}; a stumbling-block, but only figuratively (fall, enticement [idol]); ruin, stumbling-block.

h4385.definition: from {{h3789}}; a thing written, the characters, or a document (letter, copy, edict, poem); writing.

h4387.definition: from {{h3799}}; an engraving, i.e. (techn.) a poem; Michtam.

h4388.definition: from {{h3806}}; a mortar; by analogy, a socket (of a tooth); hollow place, mortar.

h4389.definition: the same as {{h4388}}; dell; the Maktesh, a place in Jerusalem; Maktesh.

h4390.definition: or מָלָא; (Esther 7:5), a primitive root; to fill or (intransitively) be full of, in a wide application (literally and figuratively); accomplish, confirm,   consecrate, be at an end, be expired, be fenced, fill, fulfil, (be, become, × draw, give in, go) full(-ly, -ly set, tale), (over-) flow, fulness, furnish, gather (selves, together), presume, replenish, satisfy, set, space, take a (hand-) full,   have wholly.

h4391.definition: (Aramaic) corresponding to {{h4390}}; to fill; fill, be full.

h4392.definition: from {{h4390}}; full (literally or figuratively) or filling (literally); also (concretely) fulness; adverbially, fully; × she that was with child, fill(-ed, -ed with), full(-ly), multitude, as is worth.

h4393.definition: rarely מְלוֹא; or מְלוֹ; (Ezekiel 41:8), from {{h4390}}; fulness (literally or figuratively); × all along, × all that is (there-) in, fill, (× that whereof...was) full, fulness, (hand-) full, multitude.

h4394.definition: from {{h4390}}; a fulfilling (only in plural), i.e. (literally) a setting (of gems), or (technically) consecration (also concretely, a dedicatory sacrifice); consecration, be set.

h4395.definition: feminine of {{h4392}}; something fulfilled, i.e. abundance (of produce); (first of ripe) fruit, fulness.

h4396.definition: feminine of {{h4394}}; a filling, i.e. setting (of gems); enclosing, setting.

h4397.definition: from an unused root meaning to despatch as a deputy; a messenger; specifically, of God, i.e. an angel (also a prophet, priest or teacher); ambassador, angel, king, messenger.

h4399.definition: from the same as {{h4397}}; properly, deputyship, i.e. ministry; generally, employment (never servile) or work (abstractly or concretely); also property (as the result of labor); business,   cattle,   industrious, occupation, (  -pied),   officer, thing (made), use, (manner of) work((-man), -manship).

h4400.definition: from the same as {{h4397}}; a message; message.
